      "SummaryText": "n a estimate population of 100 residents. The meteorological conditions , stability D,with a wind speed of 3 m/sec.\nThe plant operators is trained on the job once a year before certification. To keep the certification in effect ,24 hrs of training is required every two years. Operators attend a yearly seminar an training courses to obtain the required training hrs. Training of the community response personnel, fire fighters are trained to the awareness level and 10% are trained to the operation level.\nIn the case of a release , radio station WRVK-AM (1460) will be utilized  to notify residents whether to evacuate or stay indoors for the duration . This will depend on the size of release and the travel. Also police, fire personnel will go door-to-door to insure the evacuation of all effected residents. Schools and churches will be used as sheltersif the necessity arise. The incident commander will autherized re-entry of evacuated areas.\nThe plants E R plan has been reveiwed by the LEPC. Exercises must be conducted on a four year cycle. Functional exercises must be conducted during 3 or 4 years, but a full scale exercise must be conducted during one year of the cycle. Local officals are encouraged to include hazardous materials problems in the exercise.\nThey have not been no accident in the past five years."
    },
    {
